import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Body_Mass__g_'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Species'] == 'Adelie']['Body_Mass__g_'], 
                data[data['Species'] == 'Chinstrap']['Body_Mass__g_'], 
                data[data['Species'] == 'Gentoo']['Body_Mass__g_']], 
               labels=['Adelie', 'Chinstrap', 'Gentoo'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of body mass among the different penguin species?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Sex', 'Beak_Length__mm_'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    colors = {'MALE':'blue', 'FEMALE':'red', '.':'green'}
    ax.scatter(data['Sex'], data['Beak_Length__mm_'], c=data['Sex'].apply(lambda x: colors[x]))
    ax.set_xlabel('Gender')
    ax.set_ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    ax.set_title('How does the beak length vary by gender?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="Species", y="Beak_Depth__mm_", data=data, palette="Set3", ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel("Species")
    ax.set_ylabel("Beak Depth (mm)")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of beak depth among the different penguin species?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Body_Mass__g_', 'Island'])
    data = data.groupby(['Island'])['Body_Mass__g_'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Island'], data['Body_Mass__g_'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Island')
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    ax.set_title('How does body mass vary by island?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
